HEADWORD: Linnæite
<hw>Lin*n⟦ae⟧"ite</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧n*n⟦emac⟧"⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Linn⟦ae⟧an</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral
of pale steel-gray color and metallic luster, occurring in isometric
crystals, and also massive. It is a sulphide of cobalt containing some
nickel or copper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

